org.sensorhub.api.data

Class FoiEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sensorhub.api.common.Event<EventTypeEnum>
      • org.sensorhub.api.common.EntityEvent<FoiEvent.Type>
        • org.sensorhub.api.data.FoiEvent

  • public class FoiEvent
extends EntityEvent<FoiEvent.Type>

    Type of event generated when a new FOI is being targeted by a sensor or process. It is immutable and carries feature data by reference.

    Since:
    Apr 23, 2015
    Author:
    Alex Robin

        Creates a FoiEvent.Type.NEW_FOI event with only the feature ID
        Parameters:
        timeStamp - time of event generation (unix time in milliseconds, base 1970)
        srcModule - module that generated the event
        foiID - ID of feature of interest
        startTime - time at which observation of the FoI started (julian time in seconds, base 1970)
